#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.44"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.44:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.44:0.2"
msgid "5. Akkosavagga"
msgstr "5. Abuse"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 44. Kusinārasutta → kusinārāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an10.44:0.3"
msgid "44. Kusinārasutta"
msgstr "44. At Kusināra"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.44:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kusinārāyaṃ viharati baliharaṇe vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Kusināra, in the Forest of Offerings."

msgctxt "an10.44:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an10.44:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an10.44:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an10.44:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an10.44:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Codakena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ "
"paccavekkhitvā pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant who wants to accuse another should first check five "
"things in themselves and establish five things in themselves."

msgctxt "an10.44:2.2"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā ajjhattaṃ paccavekkhitabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should they check in themselves?"

msgctxt "an10.44:2.3"
msgid ""
"Codakena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "A mendicant who wants to accuse another should check this:"

msgctxt "an10.44:2.4"
msgid ""
"‘parisuddhakāyasamācāro nu khomhi, parisuddhenamhi kāyasamācārena "
"samannāgato acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena."
msgstr ""
"‘Is my bodily behavior pure? Do I have pure bodily behavior that is "
"impeccable and irreproachable?"

msgctxt "an10.44:2.5"
msgid "Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?"
msgstr "Is this thing found in me or not?’"

msgctxt "an10.44:2.6"
msgid ""
"No ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti parisuddhena "
"kāyasamācārena samannāgato acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena, tassa bhavanti vattāro:"
msgstr "If it’s not, there will be people who say:"

msgctxt "an10.44:2.7"
msgid "‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā kāyikaṃ sikkhassū’ti, itissa bhavanti vattāro."
msgstr "‘Come on, venerable, train your own bodily behavior first.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.44:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ "
"paccavekkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant who wants to accuse another should check this:"

msgctxt "an10.44:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘parisuddhavacīsamācāro nu khomhi, parisuddhenamhi vacīsamācārena "
"samannāgato acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena."
msgstr ""
"‘Is my verbal behavior pure? Do I have pure verbal behavior that is "
"impeccable and irreproachable?"

msgctxt "an10.44:3.3"
msgid "Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?"
msgstr "Is this thing found in me or not?’"

msgctxt "an10.44:3.4"
msgid ""
"No ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti parisuddhena "
"vacīsamācārena samannāgato acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena, tassa bhavanti vattāro:"
msgstr "If it’s not, there will be people who say:"

msgctxt "an10.44:3.5"
msgid "‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā vācasikaṃ sikkhassū’ti, itissa bhavanti vattāro."
msgstr "‘Come on, venerable, train your own verbal behavior first.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.80"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an10.44:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ "
"paccavekkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant who wants to accuse another should check this:"

msgctxt "an10.44:4.2"
msgid "‘mettaṃ nu kho me cittaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ sabrahmacārīsu anāghātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Is my heart established in love for my spiritual companions, without "
"resentment?"

msgctxt "an10.44:4.3"
msgid "Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?"
msgstr "Is this thing found in me or not?’"

msgctxt "an10.44:4.4"
msgid ""
"No ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ cittaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu "
"anāghātaṃ, tassa bhavanti vattāro:"
msgstr "If it’s not, there will be people who say:"

msgctxt "an10.44:4.5"
msgid ""
"‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā sabrahmacārīsu mettaṃ cittaṃ upaṭṭhāpehī’ti, itissa "
"bhavanti vattāro."
msgstr ""
"‘Come on, venerable, establish your heart in love for your spiritual "
"companions first.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an10.44:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ "
"paccavekkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant who wants to accuse another should check this:"

msgctxt "an10.44:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘bahussuto nu khomhi sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā "
"majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpā me dhammā bahussutā honti "
"dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā."
msgstr ""
"‘Am I very learned, remembering and keeping what I’ve learned? These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"entirely full and pure. Am I very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and "
"comprehending them theoretically?"

msgctxt "an10.44:5.3"
msgid "Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?"
msgstr "Is this thing found in me or not?’"

msgctxt "an10.44:5.4"
msgid ""
"No ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te "
"dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ "
"kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā "
"bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā "
"suppaṭividdhā, tassa bhavanti vattāro:"
msgstr "If it’s not, there will be people who say:"

msgctxt "an10.44:5.5"
msgid "‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā āgamaṃ pariyāpuṇassū’ti, itissa bhavanti vattāro."
msgstr "‘Come on, venerable, memorize the scriptures first.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.81"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an10.44:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ "
"paccavekkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant who wants to accuse another should check this:"

msgctxt "an10.44:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘ubhayāni kho pana me pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni "
"suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso."
msgstr ""
"‘Have both monastic codes been passed down to me in detail, well analyzed, "
"well mastered, and well judged in both the rules and accompanying material?"

msgctxt "an10.44:6.3"
msgid "Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?"
msgstr "Is this thing found in me or not?’"

msgctxt "an10.44:6.4"
msgid ""
"No ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ubhayāni pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti "
"suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso, ‘idaṃ "
"panāyasmā, kattha vuttaṃ bhagavatā’ti, iti puṭṭho na sampāyissati."
msgstr "If it’s not, there will be people who say:"

msgctxt "an10.44:6.5"
msgid "Tassa bhavanti vattāro:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.44:6.6"
msgid "‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā vinayaṃ sikkhassū’ti, itissa bhavanti vattāro."
msgstr "‘Come on, venerable, train in the code of conduct first.’"

msgctxt "an10.44:6.7"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā ajjhattaṃ paccavekkhitabbā."
msgstr "These are the five things they should check in themselves."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an10.44:7.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should they establish in themselves?"

msgctxt "an10.44:7.2"
msgid "‘Kālena vakkhāmi, no akālena;"
msgstr "‘I will speak at the right time, not at the wrong time."

msgctxt "an10.44:7.3"
msgid "bhūtena vakkhāmi, no abhūtena;"
msgstr "I will speak truthfully, not falsely."

msgctxt "an10.44:7.4"
msgid "saṇhena vakkhāmi, no pharusena;"
msgstr "I will speak gently, not harshly."

msgctxt "an10.44:7.5"
msgid "atthasaṃhitena vakkhāmi, no anatthasaṃhitena;"
msgstr "I will speak beneficially, not harmfully."

msgctxt "an10.44:7.6"
msgid "mettacitto vakkhāmi, no dosantaro’ti—"
msgstr "I will speak lovingly, not from secret hate.’"

msgctxt "an10.44:7.7"
msgid "ime pañca dhammā ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbā."
msgstr "These are the five things they should establish in themselves."

msgctxt "an10.44:7.8"
msgid ""
"Codakena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ "
"paccavekkhitvā ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who wants to accuse another should first check these five things "
"in themselves and establish these five things in themselves.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.44:7.9"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
